  "prompt": "What is the salary of an RTO officer?",
  "response": "The salary of an RTO (Regional Transport Office) officer in India can vary based on factors such as the state government pay scales, level of the officer (e.g., Assistant RTO, Deputy RTO, or RTO), and years of experience. Generally:\n\n1. **Assistant RTO**: Entry-level officers may earn between \u20b935,000 to \u20b950,000 per month.\n2. **Deputy RTO**: Mid-level officers may earn between \u20b950,000 to \u20b980,000 per month.\n3. **RTO (Head of the Office)**: Senior officers may earn between \u20b980,000 to \u20b91,50,000 per month or more, depending on the state and seniority.\n\nThese figures are approximate and include basic pay, grade pay, and other allowances like Dearness Allowance (DA), House Rent Allowance (HRA), and Travel Allowance (TA).\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, it is best to refer to the official state government notifications or pay commission guidelines.",
